The bat populations in Scotland and throughout the United Kingdom have fallen considerably over the last century.
These animals are threatened by construction and development works that affect the dormitories and make habitat scarce.
Wind turbines and lightning are also a threat, together with the moss-papers and some chemical treatments of building materials, as well as attacks of domestic cats.
